RTRS - Palmer wants to remove ANI directors . Ross Palmer , voted off the board of Australian National Industries Ltd ( ANI ) last month , said on Friday he had sought an extraordinary general meeting of the engineering company to remove two directors , Peter Joseph and Howard Stack . Palmer , the largest individual shareholder in Sydney - based ANI with a five percent stake , said his private company would canvass other major shareholders to decide on suitable replacements for Joseph and Stack . Joseph was instrumental in having Palmer dismissed from the board in a vote at last month ' s annual meeting . 
